            . I am a <rs id="t18310908-385-viclabel1981" type="occupation">carpenter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-385-victim2758 t18310908-385-viclabel1981"></join>. On the 12th of July, about eleven o'clock in the morning, I went with Worledge to get some beer - we left our tools in a new building at <placeName id="t18310908-385-crimeloc1982">Stepney</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-385-crimeloc1982" type="placeName" value="Stepney"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-385-crimeloc1982" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-385-off1979 t18310908-385-crimeloc1982"></join>, and left the prisoner there; we returned in about ten minutes, found the door shut, and the things gone - nobody could come there without his knowledge - he was still there - we had shut our tools up in the house we worked in - we found them in pawn in about half an hour, in the Commercial-road; from what the pawnbroker said, we went over to the prisoner, and I said"You have been pawning my tools, give me the duplicate;" he denied having the duplicate, or knowing any thing of the tools - he went into one of the houses to get his coat to go away - I detained him, and when the constable took him, he took the duplicates from his pocket, and threw them on the ground - the bit, which I had left in my stock, we found in his pocket.</p>
